<h1>@HI{{te/shinaide}} (accompany)</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@Vte{{}}</strong> @V2{{}}
<li> <strong>@Vnai{{}}@HI{{de}}</strong> @V2{{}}
</ol>
</dl>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@Vte{{}}</strong> can be used to indicate something that accompanies another action.
Similarly, <strong>@Vnai{{}} @HI{{de}}</strong> can be used to indicate that something does not
accompany another action.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{shouyuuwo <strong>tsukete</strong> @KJ{{eat}}bemasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      We eat it with soy sauce.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{shouyuuwo <strong>tsukenaide</strong> @KJ{{eat}}bemasu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      We eat it without soy sauce.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

